{"word":"ἐρωτάω","slug":"ἐρωτάω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἐρωτάω</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ἔρομαι'><el>ἔρομαι</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to ask</i>, <el>τινά τι</el> something <i>of</i> one, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>:—<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to be asked</i>, <el>τι</el> <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><el>ἐρ. τι</el> <i>to ask about</i> a thing, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>:— <a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a>, <el>τὸ ἐρωτηθέν, τὸ ἐρωτώμενον</el> <i>the question</i>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>to enquire of</i> a person, <i>question</i> him, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>:—<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to be questioned</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>III. </b>= <a href='S:αἰτέω'><el>αἰτέω</el></a>, <i>to ask</i>, <a href='S:id est'>i. e.</a> <i>to beg, solicit</i>, <b><a href='S:New Testament'>NTest.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}